  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Pulmonary rehabilitation has been established as an evidence-based and recommended therapy in
      patients following lung transplantation. Exercise training has been shown to be a cornerstone
      of an inpatient rehabilitation program to reduce muscle dysfunction and improve exercise
      performance. In our study we will investigate the benefit of a whole body vibration training
      in addition to a standard pulmonary rehabilitation program that includes endurance and
      strength training. We will include a total of 140 patients (70 patients &lt; 1 year after lung
      Transplantation and 70 patients &gt; 1 year after lung Transplantation). Our hypothesis is that
      an addtitional whole body vibration training produces a greater benefit to exercise capacity
      in lung transplantat patients (LTx).
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
